  "prompt": "Who writes the best class notes in IIT, Bombay?",
  "response": "The question of who writes the best class notes in IIT Bombay is subjective and can vary depending on personal preferences and the specific subject being studied. However, many students at IIT Bombay often share notes and collaborate through various online platforms, study groups, and student-run initiatives. Some well-known platforms where IIT Bombay students share notes and resources include:\n\n1. **InstiClassNotes:** A student-run website where students can upload and download class notes for various courses.\n2. **Academic Council Resources:** The academic council often collects and shares high-quality notes and study materials for different courses.\n3. **Departmental Forums and Groups:** Many departments have their own forums or WhatsApp groups where students share notes and help each other.\n\nWhile it's difficult to pinpoint a single person who writes the \"best\" notes, you might find high-quality notes from top-performing students or those who are particularly thorough in their note-taking. Connecting with classmates and seniors, attending study group sessions, and exploring resources shared by student organizations can help you access some of the best notes available.",
